Package org.daisy.streamline.api.config

Class ConfigurationsCatalog

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.daisy.streamline.api.config.ConfigurationsCatalog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationsCatalogService
    public class ConfigurationsCatalog
extends Object
implements ConfigurationsCatalogService
    Provides a catalog of configurations available to the input system. The catalog implementation can be overridden if a different behavior is desired. In most cases, the default configuration catalog should suffice. To override this class, extend it and add a reference to the implementation to the java service registry. Provides a default configurations catalog. The default configurations catalog will scan the service registry for configurations providers and collect the keys of every provider. If more than one provider contains the same key, the most recently added will be used, and a debug message will be sent to the log.
